cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.CY 

The paper discusses the integration of blockchain with 5G networks, which falls under the category of network infrastructure and protocols. Therefore, cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the potential of blockchain for privacy and security provision, which falls under the category of cryptography and security, making cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) the second likely sub-category. The paper also discusses cloud/edge computing, Software Defined Networks, Network Function Virtualization, Network Slicing, and D2D communications, which fall under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing, making cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) the third likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the applications of blockchain in various domains, such as smart healthcare, smart city, smart transportation, smart grid, and UAVs, which fall under the category of data structures and algorithms, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) the fourth likely sub-category. Lastly, the paper discusses the opportunities of blockchain to important 5G services, ranging from spectrum management, network virtualization, resource management to interference management, federated learning, privacy, and security provision, which fall under the category of computers and society, making cs.CY (Computers and Society) the fifth likely sub-category.
